The village is located near Kyiv and was occupied by Russian forces for weeks. Taras Didych, head of the Dmytrivka community that includes Buzova and several other nearby villages, told Ukrainian television that the bodies were found in a ditch close to a petrol station. He said: "'Now, we are returning to life, but during the occupation we had our 'hotspots', many civilians died." Another 50 bodies were found along the road near Buzova. The victims had been shot execution-style at close range. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...